<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,888,1502]" box="[189,938,957,982]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Etymology. The specific name is derived from the 
<typeStatus box="[730,776,958,982]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality; noun.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,888,1502]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Diagnosis. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Deeleman-Reinhold, 1995" authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="1995" box="[629,1109,992,1016]" class="Arachnida" family="Ochyroceratidae" genus="Speocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suratthaniensis">
<emphasis box="[629,820,992,1016]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. suratthaniensis</emphasis>
Deeleman-Reinhold, 1995
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished by the large, oval spermathecae and the distinct bending of the tip of the afferent spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1241,1027,1051]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="18.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-62@18.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 13. Speocera bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366949/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 13A–B</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deeleman-Reinhold" authorityYear="1995" box="[1260,1451,1027,1051]" class="Arachnida" family="Ochyroceratidae" genus="Speocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="suratthaniensis">
<emphasis box="[1260,1451,1027,1051]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">S. suratthaniensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females have small, oval spermathecae and a straight tip of the afferent spermathecae (Deeleman-Reinhold, 1995: figs 293– 294).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,888,1502]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Description. Female. Total length 1.06; carapace length 0.51; carapace width 0.42; abdomen length 0.56; abdomen width 0.43. Prosoma: carapace pyriform, narrowing gradually anteriorly; shiny, light yellow, suffused with purplish pattern (
<figureCitation box="[144,242,1200,1224]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="18.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-62@18.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 13. Speocera bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366949/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
); pars cephalica flat; fovea not visible. Sternum light yellow, suffused with purplish color, as long as wide (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="18.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-62@18.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 13. Speocera bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366949/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
). Endites light yellow suffused with purplish tinge; with serrula; labium light yellow suffused with purplish tinge. Clypeus nearly vertical; short. Chelicerae light yellow; promargin with a series of six teeth reaching the lamina; retromargin with two very small denticles (
<figureCitation box="[480,581,1304,1328]" captionStart="Figure 58" captionStartId="73.[154,217,2026,2048]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,233,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-98@73.[188,1398,233,2011]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="Figure 58. Female chelicerae of Speocera spp., anterior view. A. S. balikpapan Li &amp; Li sp. nov. B. S. batang Li &amp; Li sp. nov. C. S. bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov. D. S. cuyapo Li &amp; Li sp. nov. E. S. dongjing Li &amp; Li sp. nov. F. S. griswoldi Li &amp; Li sp. nov. G. S. huifengi Li &amp; Li sp. nov. H. S. huisun Li &amp; Li sp. nov. I. S. melinh Li &amp; Li sp. nov. J. S. tabuk Li &amp; Li sp. nov. Scale bars=0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367045/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 58C</figureCitation>
). Eyes: six contiguous eyes surrounded by black pigmentation; 
<collectionCode box="[1289,1344,1304,1327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">PME</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode box="[1399,1451,1304,1328]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">ALE</collectionCode>
subequal, 
<collectionCode box="[246,293,1339,1362]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">PLE</collectionCode>
largest (
<figureCitation box="[388,487,1339,1363]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="18.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-62@18.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 13. Speocera bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366949/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
). Opisthosoma oval; purplish (
<figureCitation box="[822,922,1339,1363]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="18.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-62@18.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 13. Speocera bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366949/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
). Legs missing. Genitalia. Internal genitalia with afferent spermathecae long, straight, not extending past the sides of the abdomen, distally with a distinct bend (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1438,1373,1397]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="18.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-62@18.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 13. Speocera bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366949/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 13B</figureCitation>
); spermathecae large, oval (
<figureCitation box="[414,514,1408,1432]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="18.[155,218,2038,2060]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,234,2004]" captionTargetId="figure-62@18.[189,1398,234,2011]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 13. Speocera bontoc Li &amp; Li sp. nov., holotype, female. A. Genitalia, dorsal view. B. Genitalia, ventral view. C–E. Habitus, dorsal, ventral and lateral views. Scale bars: A–B=0.05mm; C–E=0.30 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366949/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,888,1502]" box="[189,370,1443,1467]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[136,1452,888,1502]" box="[189,707,1477,1502]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Distribution. Known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[568,614,1478,1502]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
